This is a gstreamer plugin for recognition
of specific images in a video stream.

The video stream can be a video file 
or a video stream
and the collection of images 
can be changed dynamically 
sending a message to the plugin.

The plugin uses OpenCV for the recognition of images.

To use it on Ubuntu, first install the dependencies :
sudo apt-get install gstreamer-0.10 gstreamer-base-0.10 gstreamer-plugins-base-0.10 opencv

Then compile the plugins with :

sudo ./configure --prefix=/usr
sudo make
sudo make-install

Then launch it with a pipe like :

gst-launch filesrc location=data/slides.mp4  ! decodebin ! ffmpegcolorspace ! imgspot imgdir=data/images algorithm=histogram ! ffmpegcolorspace ! xvimagesink

For any more information or support, contact ydegoyon@gmail.com.
